{"article_id":"PMdMc7cnpxJsZCRJ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama 's decision","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"to publicly support same-sex marriage","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"may have changed the minds of some Americans ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"according to a national poll .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"But in states","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"that will vote on the issue in November ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"the impact has been mixed .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Gay-marriage advocates say","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"they have raised more money","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"and attracted additional campaign volunteers since the president 's historic announcement in May .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"But opponents downplay Obama 's potential impact , beyond serving to mobilize their conservative base .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Four states will ask voters to weigh in on same-sex marriage , with the possibility","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"that it could be upheld as law in Maryland , Maine and Washington state .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"In the fourth state , Minnesota ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"where gay marriage already has been outlawed ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"voters will consider a constitutional amendment","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"to ban it .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Most polling has shown","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"a majority of Americans have come to support gay marriage ,","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"but the issue has failed at the ballot box every time .","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"In the 32 states","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"in which voters have had a say ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"they have rejected it .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"In the six states and Washington , D.C. ,","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"where same-sex marriage is legal ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"it came through legislative or court action .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"As the first president","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"to endorse same-sex marriage ,","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"Obama does so","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"while the issue remains divisive and politically risky for him .","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"To gauge the potential impact of Obama 's decision ,","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"some historians compare it to President Kennedy 's 1963 speech","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"in which he stood up for civil rights as `` a moral issue ''","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"or President Lincoln 's opposition to slavery .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Kennedy 's approval rating dropped to its worst low ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"and Lincoln was met with the Civil War .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"`` The short-run political costs can be devastating , ''","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"says Barbara Perry , a presidential scholar at the University of Virginia 's Miller Center .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"`` But we want our presidents to lead ,","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"right ?","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"If a president can put aside politics","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"and make these kinds of decisions for moral reasons","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"- and if they can stay the course-","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"history regards them well . ''","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"In Maryland ,","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"where voters will decide whether to uphold a same-sex law","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"passed this year ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"opponents and supporters alike say","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"that Obama has significantly influenced the debate .","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"In March , a Public Policy Polling sampling of Maryland voters showed","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"52 percent said","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"they would uphold the new law in November ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"and 44 percent said","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"they would repeal it .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"Two weeks after Obama 's announcement ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"PPP found","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"support had climbed to 57 percent","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"and opposition had dropped to 37 percent .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"The 12-point swing was driven by African-Americans ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"whose support for the law jumped to 55 percent , up from 39 percent in March .","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"The size of the shift was unexpected","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"because blacks in other states have consistently voted against gay marriage ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"citing deeply held religious objections to homosexuality .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Black voters hold considerable influence in Maryland ,","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"where they made up a quarter of the electorate in 2008 .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"`` The African-American community supports the president very strongly ,","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"and for the president to take a stand on the issue was something","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"we think","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"is going to be important","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"in helping other African-Americans come around , ''","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"says Josh Levin , campaign manager for Marylanders for Marriage Equality ,","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"which is working to preserve the law .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"The campaign says","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"it has attracted about 6,500 new volunteers in the past month","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"and received three times more donations than in April and May combined .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"( The campaign declined to provide actual figures . )","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Derek McCoy , executive director of Maryland Marriage Alliance , said","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"Obama 's position also helped fuel his group 's signature drive ,","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"which forced the referendum .","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"`` What it has done is energize people to uphold what has been the definition of marriage , ''","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"McCoy says .","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"`` What he 's also done is stir up a lot of people in the Democratic Party to say","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"'Enough is enough .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"I 'm drawing the line on this issue . ' ``","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"In Washington state , the new same-sex marriage law was scheduled to take effect June 7 .","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"But the day before , opponents submitted enough signatures","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"to force a referendum .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"Joseph Backholm , the chairman of Preserve Marriage Washington ,","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"which opposes gay marriage","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"and collected the signatures for the referendum ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"says","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"`` it 's beyond dispute at this point that polling on the issue of gay marriage is totally unreliable . ''","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"Backholm predicts","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"Obama 's announcement `` will ultimately be of no consequence , ''","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"although he says","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"it did initially trigger `` a slight uptick '' in donations to the campaign and a `` dramatic increase '' in volunteers","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"gathering signatures .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"The group has raised roughly $ 105,000 ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"Backholm says .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"`` There are a lot of people","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"who have never been involved in a political issue","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"that are now getting involved","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"because they understand the significance of this as a culturally defining issue , ''","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"Backholm says ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"that more than 1,500 churches have signed on .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"The leading gay-marriage proponent , Washington United for Marriage , on Monday said","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"June fundraising delivered its highest monthly sum , $ 952,267 .","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"A pair of $ 100,000 donations came from Microsoft co-founder Bill Gates and current Chief Executive Steve Ballmer ,","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"bringing total donations to more than $ 2 million ,","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"according to campaign manager Zach Silk .","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"Silk said","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"it helped","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"that Obama visited the state on the day after his announcement .","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"And ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"Gay Pride Month celebrations in June raised the intensity of supporters .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"Also in June , a Public Policy Polling survey found","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"that for the first time in a year","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"of sampling , a slight majority of Washington state voters favored the legalization of gay marriage .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"`` I think","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"there 's a feeling in the country and here in Washington","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"that we 're at tipping point on this issue , ''","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"says Silk .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"With this year 's initiative , Maine becomes the first state","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"in which supporters of same-sex marriage , rather than opponents , have put the issue on the ballot .","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"Voters in 2009 overturned a law","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"passed by the state Legislature ,","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"but supporters never stopped organizing .","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"`` We have n't seen much of an effect in our polling ,","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"nor would I expect that to be the case , ''","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"says Matt McTighe , campaign manager for Mainers United for Marriage , a coalition of groups","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"advocating gay marriage .","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"`` This is just such a personal issue","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"that it 's something","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"people here can only come to support on their own terms . ''","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"Carroll Conley Jr. is executive director of the Christian Civic League of Maine and a board member of Protect Marriage Maine ,","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"which leads the opposition .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"He says ,","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"`` Of course it makes a difference","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"if the president of the United States comes down on any issue .","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"There 's no doubt","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"it created dialogue . ''","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"But ,","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"Conley says ,","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"he 's seen no noticeable shift in voter opinions .","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"McTighe says","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"organizers `` meet people where they are ''","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"and have had personal conversations with more than 100,000 voters ,","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"targeting those","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"who are undecided .","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"He says","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"2012 was chosen","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"to try to take advantage of the usually larger turnout for presidential elections ,","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"which attract more young voters","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"who tend to support gay marriage .","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"A June poll by NPR member station WBUR and the MassINC Polling Group found","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"55 percent of Maine voters favored a law","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"that would provide marriage licenses to same-sex couples","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"but exempt religious institutions from being required to perform the nuptials .","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"Thirty-six percent opposed it","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"and 9 percent were undecided","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"or refused to answer .","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"Opponents are relying heavily on turning out church congregations and on fundraising help from the National Organization for Marriage .","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"Conley says","depth":7},{"id":165,"text":"he expects to be outspent by the same-sex marriage campaign ,","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"which","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"he believes","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"carries the `` weight","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"of changing people 's minds . '' `` The most private response","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"that a person is allowed","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"is at the voter 's booth , ''","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"Conley says .","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"`` That 's what comes out surprisingly more conservative","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"than what we see in polls . ''","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":349,"left":218,"right":348,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":200,"right":217,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":191,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":185,"right":190,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":181,"right":184,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":181,"left":178,"right":180,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":178,"left":177,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":176,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":176,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":179,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":179,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":183,"right":10,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":183,"left":7,"right":182,"